WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:03.404
You're witnessing
the power of Empire.

00:03.437 --> 00:05.906
I'm Cookie Lyon, baby.
I'm unforgettable.

00:05.939 --> 00:07.675
Catch all-new episodes
Wednesdays.

00:07.708 --> 00:09.210
And check out
our other Fox programs--

00:09.243 --> 00:12.012
Star, The Gifted,
and Lethal Weapon.

00:12.046 --> 00:14.548
That was the best idea
you've had all day.

00:14.582 --> 00:15.749
Only on Fox.

00:17.351 --> 00:19.753
-Previously on Empire...
-You had a mild heart attack.

00:19.787 --> 00:21.255
You might not be so lucky
the next time.

00:21.289 --> 00:23.657
-The car bomb. It was me.
-(yells)

00:23.691 --> 00:25.526
-I'm sorry.
-I hope it's enough.

00:25.559 --> 00:26.927
I'm done apologizing.
I'm done

00:26.960 --> 00:28.662
doing stupid interviews
that I don't want to do.

00:28.696 --> 00:30.231
Got room for only one man
in your life.

00:30.264 --> 00:31.832
He's sitting
right in front of you.

00:31.865 --> 00:34.102
-"Desperate" is what you've
made us.
-Everyone will be paid

00:34.135 --> 00:36.003
once I push this deal through
at Empire,

00:36.036 --> 00:37.271
and we'll all be back
where we belong.

00:37.305 --> 00:39.073
When do we tell the Lyons
that I'm buying Empire?

00:39.107 --> 00:41.209
-Leave the Lyons to me.
-You let Eddie into Empire,

00:41.242 --> 00:43.010
and he's about to steal it
from under you.

00:43.043 --> 00:44.545
I stepped in when you needed me.

00:44.578 --> 00:46.046
I saved your ass!

00:46.080 --> 00:47.981
Get the hell out of my house.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.384
Come on, Ma.

00:50.418 --> 00:51.919
Want to make sure
you get in, Ma.

00:51.952 --> 00:53.921
Boy, I had a heart attack.

00:53.954 --> 00:55.856
Okay? I still got both my legs.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.925
Oh, no offense, Lucious.

00:57.958 --> 00:59.293
LUCIOUS:
None taken.

00:59.327 --> 01:01.429
Um, we're ready.

01:01.462 --> 01:03.097
JAMAL:
All right, Ma,

01:03.131 --> 01:04.932
we got Chef Rahim here,

01:04.965 --> 01:07.401
who has made you the healthiest

01:07.435 --> 01:09.103
vegan Cajun soul food.

01:09.137 --> 01:11.539
Yeah, well, one of them words
don't belong in a sentence

01:11.572 --> 01:13.274
with the other words,
but whatever.

01:13.307 --> 01:15.543
LUCIOUS:
Honey, I have something for you.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.711
What is this now?

01:17.745 --> 01:19.880
It's a fitness bracelet.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.215
What it does is it monitors

01:21.249 --> 01:23.050
your heart rate,
your blood pressure.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.153
If you get too excited,
an alarm will go off

01:25.186 --> 01:28.156
and, via an app,
it will alert both our phones.

01:28.189 --> 01:30.124
-Okay?
-Mm. So, basically,

01:30.158 --> 01:32.726
it's a fancy ankle monitor.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.295
I'm on house arrest. Lord.

01:34.328 --> 01:36.997
You're on love arrest
until you get better.

01:37.030 --> 01:38.999
JUANITA:
Delivery.

01:39.032 --> 01:42.136
From Mr. Eddie Barker.

01:44.872 --> 01:47.808
Eddie wants us to know that he's

01:47.841 --> 01:50.611
sincerely apologetic
for his outburst.

01:50.644 --> 01:53.481
-Yeah, he got to be embarrassed.
-Was it that bad?

01:53.514 --> 01:55.249
I thought he was gonna stroke
out on the floor over there.

01:55.283 --> 01:58.018
Think about it-- before we
roped him into all our mess,

01:58.051 --> 01:59.653
he was retired,

01:59.687 --> 02:02.256
on the golf course,
counting his money.

02:02.290 --> 02:05.025
Now, who knows,
maybe he just got overzealous.

02:05.058 --> 02:06.994
-Well...
-How you like
your breakfast, Ma?

02:07.027 --> 02:09.463
I don't know how he did it.
This is good.

02:09.497 --> 02:12.300
-Yeah.
-See, told you some good
might come out of all this.

02:12.333 --> 02:13.767
When's the last time
we all sat down

02:13.801 --> 02:15.135
and ate some breakfast together?

02:15.169 --> 02:16.970
COOKIE:
We? All of us ain't here.

02:17.004 --> 02:18.872
-Where's Andre?
-Told him not to come.

02:18.906 --> 02:21.342
Right.
So I don't get to see my son

02:21.375 --> 02:23.143
'cause you don't want him here.

02:23.177 --> 02:24.845
He tried to kill me, Cookie.

02:24.878 --> 02:26.947
Hey, you know what, Lucious?
I hate to break it to you,

02:26.980 --> 02:30.184
but everybody at this table,
at one point, wanted you dead.

02:33.020 --> 02:36.357
Look, I... I know
you're doing all of this

02:36.390 --> 02:37.958
'cause you love me,

02:37.991 --> 02:39.627
but if you really want
to heal my heart, Lucious,

02:39.660 --> 02:41.629
please talk to Andre.

02:41.662 --> 02:44.131
Please give him a chance.

02:44.164 --> 02:45.165
Okay?

02:49.002 --> 02:50.571
* We play the game *

02:50.604 --> 02:53.006
* Every time where nobody *

02:53.040 --> 02:54.908
-Keep it sexy. Keep it sexy.
-* Wanting to say *

02:54.942 --> 02:56.544
* But I'm thinking that *

02:56.577 --> 02:57.711
* Maybe it's time *

02:57.745 --> 03:00.147
* For a change, for you and I *

03:00.180 --> 03:01.949
CHOREOGRAPHER:
Let's go.

03:03.717 --> 03:05.085
Hey.

03:05.118 --> 03:06.754
* Pull me, pull me closer *

03:08.422 --> 03:11.259
-* Love me till it's over *
-Milk it.

03:11.292 --> 03:12.893
* Stay with me
right by my side *

03:12.926 --> 03:14.895
* And we'll make it,
we'll make tonight *

03:14.928 --> 03:15.896
* Unforgettable *

03:15.929 --> 03:18.266
Let's go. Hey.

03:18.299 --> 03:20.868
* Unforgettable *

03:20.901 --> 03:23.103
-Clean up. Clean up.
-* I wanted this *

03:23.136 --> 03:25.005
* For so long *

03:25.038 --> 03:27.074
-Right here.
-* Let's make tonight
unforgettable... *

03:27.107 --> 03:28.676
Y'all keep rushing the song.

03:28.709 --> 03:30.043
Why do you keep rushing?

03:30.077 --> 03:31.078
WOMAN:
Sorry, T.

03:31.111 --> 03:32.580
Thought we were on point.

03:32.613 --> 03:34.748
Well, obviously, you weren't.

03:34.782 --> 03:36.016
Look, T, if you just stop

03:36.049 --> 03:37.685
skipping a beat,
they'd be on point.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.953
No, no. Controlling them
is your job, right?

03:39.987 --> 03:42.189
If not, then why are you here?

03:42.222 --> 03:43.757
(scoffs) You know what?
Let's just take five.

03:43.791 --> 03:45.659
Come on, ladies.

03:46.827 --> 03:48.729
What's up?

03:48.762 --> 03:50.898
Oh... Look, I know
you're going through a lot,

03:50.931 --> 03:53.701
but every time you come in,
I can't keep getting sidetracked

03:53.734 --> 03:55.803
when you need a shoulder
to cry on. I'm sorry.

03:55.836 --> 03:57.305
Ain't no tears here, mama.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.806
And get it right.

03:58.839 --> 04:00.274
I'm here to rehearse.

04:01.275 --> 04:02.943
So go ahead and move along.

04:02.976 --> 04:06.880
Actually, you-you're not on the
schedule today, Hakeem.

04:06.914 --> 04:09.883
-I don't reserve spaces we own.
-Of course you don't.

04:09.917 --> 04:12.586
Yet, and still,
we have reserved this space,

04:12.620 --> 04:15.155
so I'm gonna need you guys
to go, because we are having

04:15.188 --> 04:16.790
a super intense rehear... Hey!

04:16.824 --> 04:19.159
Excuse me! Off the snacks.
Come on.

04:19.192 --> 04:21.128
-Come on, let me walk y'all out.
-This ain't gonna work.

04:21.161 --> 04:22.296
Come on, let's go.

04:22.330 --> 04:23.964
Have a good night.
All of the cupcakes?

04:23.997 --> 04:26.266
-Thank you.
-Selfish.

04:26.300 --> 04:28.469
-Where you finna go?
-Ask her.

04:28.502 --> 04:30.438
What?

04:30.471 --> 04:32.873
She's useless, so I fired her.

04:37.611 --> 04:38.812
-(doorbell rings)
-NEWSMAN:
...families and survivors

04:38.846 --> 04:40.113
of the tragic mass shooting.

04:40.147 --> 04:42.416
The president has been
petitioned to meet with...

04:42.450 --> 04:43.751
Porsha, Miss Cookie.

04:43.784 --> 04:46.854
Ooh! Oh, thank you.

04:46.887 --> 04:48.922
I thought I was gonna have to
watch the news all day.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.425
Child, this news is depressing.

04:51.459 --> 04:53.994
-(TV turns off)
-What you got for me, huh?

04:54.027 --> 04:55.696
Got some 20 For 20 info for me?

04:55.729 --> 04:57.931
-What about Becky's A&R budget?
-I'm not supposed to

04:57.965 --> 04:59.199
bring you anything
dealing with business.

04:59.232 --> 05:01.001
That's Lucious' orders.

05:01.034 --> 05:04.538
You know what stresses me out?
Not being at Empire.

05:04.572 --> 05:06.840
I brought you some messages.

05:06.874 --> 05:09.176
Bey and J sent get well wishes,
and some chick named Asia

05:09.209 --> 05:10.878
been blowing up the phone
since you got sick.

05:10.911 --> 05:13.981
It don't say Asia, stupid.
It says Chyna.

05:14.014 --> 05:17.685
Chyna. That's what I said.

05:17.718 --> 05:19.553
She been calling every day.
Who the hell is she?

05:19.587 --> 05:21.722
We were in prison together.

05:21.755 --> 05:23.657
Oh. She wants to see you.

05:23.691 --> 05:27.961
Damn. I haven't talked to Chyna
since we got out.

05:27.995 --> 05:31.164
Well, I'll tell her
you ain't up for it.

05:31.198 --> 05:33.901
No. Call her back.

05:33.934 --> 05:35.335
Tell her I'm sending a car.

05:35.369 --> 05:37.037
-You sure?
-Mm-hmm.

05:37.070 --> 05:38.271
Okay.

05:43.176 --> 05:45.178
-Everything's starting to look
so dated now.
-Pop?

05:45.212 --> 05:48.482
-Mm-hmm.
-Pop. I need you to
take a look at this.

05:48.516 --> 05:50.083
It's your problem, man, now.

05:50.117 --> 05:51.752
You're the one who taught me
to follow my instincts.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.053
Now, ever since Eddie lost it,

05:53.086 --> 05:55.589
my instincts have been
screaming at me.

05:55.623 --> 05:58.225
He flipped out specifically
because his deal fell apart,

05:58.258 --> 06:00.461
like he personally stood
to lose, Pop.

06:03.631 --> 06:06.567
Six entities bought Empire stock
just before,

06:06.600 --> 06:08.235
when Eddie thought we were going
to announce his plan

06:08.268 --> 06:10.203
to sell Empire to Kelly Patel.

06:10.237 --> 06:12.440
Each company bought just enough
shares so that they would remain

06:12.473 --> 06:14.241
under the SEC threshold.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.109
We are a globally
traded company.

06:16.143 --> 06:18.278
Everybody buys and sells
Empire stock.

06:18.311 --> 06:20.247
That's true, Pop, true.

06:20.280 --> 06:23.283
But if the companies
were somehow connected,

06:23.316 --> 06:25.352
someone would've made
hundreds of millions

06:25.385 --> 06:26.954
on the stock valuation alone.

06:35.262 --> 06:39.032
And your instinct
says that Eddie is behind this?

06:39.066 --> 06:40.834
I know I'm right.

06:44.772 --> 06:45.906
Prove it.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.411
*

07:00.921 --> 07:02.255
Hmm.

07:04.792 --> 07:07.427
She Dragon Holdings,
Incorporated.

07:09.930 --> 07:12.232
They bought enough stock
to walk away with $15 million

07:12.265 --> 07:13.567
if Eddie's deal went through.

07:13.601 --> 07:14.968
You know the company?

07:15.002 --> 07:16.737
That's a name
that Eddie used to call his,

07:16.770 --> 07:19.940
um, second ex-wife, Celeste.

07:19.973 --> 07:23.243
She Dragon.
Okay, what about, uh...

07:23.276 --> 07:26.246
Blue-Z Ventures?

07:26.279 --> 07:28.516
You're kidding me.

07:28.549 --> 07:31.318
That was a corny quote

07:31.351 --> 07:33.286
from one of Eddie's
favorite films.

07:33.320 --> 07:36.824
He used to say,
"It's a bluesy adventure."

07:36.857 --> 07:39.459
(sighs) That's two buyers
with a link to Eddie, Pop.

07:39.493 --> 07:41.328
That's no coincidence.

07:41.361 --> 07:43.597
(sighs) I don't know, man.

07:43.631 --> 07:46.366
Eddie has enough money.

07:46.399 --> 07:49.202
I mean, why does he want to
screw me over?

07:49.236 --> 07:51.672
Let's ask Celeste.

07:51.705 --> 07:53.707
The She Dragon.

07:57.477 --> 08:00.781
I am so proud of you.

08:00.814 --> 08:03.116
I mean, all of us
back there are.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.719
I'm in here with you and them.

08:06.554 --> 08:08.221
Ooh.

08:08.255 --> 08:09.690
Uh, I got this. Thank you.

08:09.723 --> 08:12.025
(clears throat)

08:13.594 --> 08:14.728
You know, Chyna,

08:14.762 --> 08:17.665
I know you think I forgot
about you guys,

08:17.698 --> 08:19.432
but it's really not like that.

08:22.035 --> 08:25.072
I wouldn't have survived if it
weren't for you and the crew.

08:25.105 --> 08:27.474
Yeah, well, sometimes
it's just easier to

08:27.507 --> 08:29.509
not deal with life
on the inside.

08:29.543 --> 08:30.578
Yeah.
(laughs)

08:30.611 --> 08:33.246
We spent all those nights

08:33.280 --> 08:35.382
dreaming about getting out.

08:35.415 --> 08:37.685
God...

08:37.718 --> 08:40.220
Never really realizing
how hard it'll be.

08:40.253 --> 08:44.558
Mm. And no one on the outside,
like, gets you. You know?

08:44.592 --> 08:47.360
-Hmm.
-I mean, I was so used to
being on guard 24/7.

08:47.394 --> 08:49.529
You dis me, hey, we gonna fight.
(laughs)

08:49.563 --> 08:51.865
Yeah, you better calm it down,

08:51.899 --> 08:55.368
'cause one false move, they
throw your ass right back in.

08:55.402 --> 08:58.839
You remember how we used to bet
on how long chicks

08:58.872 --> 09:00.407
would be making it
on the outside?

09:00.440 --> 09:04.878
Man, I used to hate seeing them
sad faces walk back in.

09:04.912 --> 09:08.048
Well, I think the mama
was a psycho.

09:08.081 --> 09:09.783
Anybody that do this
to they own child...

09:09.817 --> 09:11.218
Yeah, well, at least
she ain't kill her.

09:11.251 --> 09:14.021
-She tried to.
-No, the mama was sick.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.623
-She had her own pain.
-Hmm.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.224
True, but still...

09:17.257 --> 09:18.558
pain makes people
do crazy things.

09:18.592 --> 09:21.929
Oh, look who's back.

09:21.962 --> 09:23.897
Five years gone,
and I still knew

09:23.931 --> 09:26.466
this bitch would end up
right back in here.

09:26.499 --> 09:28.368
Can I talk to you, Cookie?

09:28.401 --> 09:30.037
After you had me thrown in hell

09:30.070 --> 09:31.404
for your
"get out of jail free" card?

09:31.438 --> 09:33.907
-You got the wrong bitch.
-(drops book)

09:33.941 --> 09:36.209
Uh-uh. Ain't nobody getting
no write-ups today.

09:36.243 --> 09:37.477
Move on, Poundcake. Come on.

09:37.510 --> 09:38.879
Yeah, move on, Poundcake.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.882
Ain't nobody getting
written up today.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.951
I ain't messing with you,
Poundcake. You a snitch.

09:43.984 --> 09:45.052
Sit down.

09:45.085 --> 09:46.754
We reading the Bible next time,

09:46.787 --> 09:48.455
'cause y'all acting crazy.

09:48.488 --> 09:50.290
-What page are we on?
-ALL: 89.

09:50.323 --> 09:54.728
-89. Like I said,
the mama is crazy.
-Right.

09:54.762 --> 09:57.998
Poundcake still on the inside?

09:58.031 --> 10:01.001
Uh, yeah, she's still locked up.

10:01.034 --> 10:03.671
But I heard she was in hospice.

10:03.704 --> 10:07.775
Hospice? (chuckles)
What's wrong with her?

10:07.808 --> 10:09.309
Cancer.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.546
It's bad.

10:15.348 --> 10:18.551
But maybe she finally getting
what she deserved.

10:21.655 --> 10:24.291
* No more crying now *

10:24.324 --> 10:28.095
* They think our picture
is broken *

10:28.128 --> 10:30.430
* But maybe it was
out of focus *

10:30.463 --> 10:32.599
* They don't know we're gold *

10:32.632 --> 10:34.467
* They don't know
we're gold, go. *

10:34.501 --> 10:35.635
(music stops)

10:35.669 --> 10:37.537
Becky, come on.

10:37.570 --> 10:39.940
Literally, first of all,
the fans will love it.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.942
It's unexpected,
it's unapologetic.

10:41.975 --> 10:43.176
It's that new stuff.
You know what I'm saying?

10:43.210 --> 10:44.177
That's what we need.

10:44.211 --> 10:45.312
You are a true artist,

10:45.345 --> 10:48.281
and we are 100% behind you.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.350
-Thanks, y'all.
-However,

10:50.383 --> 10:53.821
we've been doing some testing,
and your fans feel differently.

10:53.854 --> 10:56.489
Testing?

10:56.523 --> 10:57.991
That's what we doing
around here now?

10:58.025 --> 10:59.359
Well, yeah, we've been testing

10:59.392 --> 11:01.528
some of our 20 For 20 releases,

11:01.561 --> 11:05.465
and that is just a bit
of feedback from them.

11:05.498 --> 11:08.068
"Angry Jamal's killing my vibe."

11:08.101 --> 11:10.637
"Who does Jamal Lyon think
he is, Migos?"

11:10.670 --> 11:13.006
This is stupid. These-these are
obviously just trolls.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.975
-Y'all know that.
-All right, but, Jamal,

11:15.008 --> 11:17.377
this bad boy narrative
is on you.

11:17.410 --> 11:20.380
It's the Warren situation,
Angelo, Robin Roberts.

11:20.413 --> 11:22.682
This sort of behavior,

11:22.716 --> 11:25.585
along with this new sound,
is just...

11:25.618 --> 11:29.189
it's not what your fans
expect or want from you.

11:29.222 --> 11:31.158
What they expect.
Okay, well-well,

11:31.191 --> 11:33.360
whatever's happening
outside of the studio, though,

11:33.393 --> 11:35.528
is not the narrative
that I'm selling. The music is.

11:35.562 --> 11:37.030
-I know.
-I guarantee you if y'all

11:37.064 --> 11:38.932
pull together, do your job,

11:38.966 --> 11:41.001
do it right,
you'll sell the record.

11:41.034 --> 11:44.237
Mm. I got to do my job.

11:44.271 --> 11:46.606
Okay, look, I'm feeling
the verses, but the hook

11:46.639 --> 11:49.109
needs a little work, so we're
gonna loop the track, let you

11:49.142 --> 11:50.610
-work it out for a minute.
All right.
-Okay.

11:50.643 --> 11:52.245
You can take five.

11:52.279 --> 11:53.580
(sighs)
You were right, man.

11:53.613 --> 11:54.915
I'm always right.

11:54.948 --> 11:56.416
What about now?

11:56.449 --> 11:58.385
I've been letting
all that Tiana stuff

11:58.418 --> 12:00.788
plus the whole thing
with my mom get to me.

12:00.821 --> 12:02.956
I got to focus on my music.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.692
So hook me up with
some bomb-ass beats, Shine.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.961
Smart man. I got you.

12:07.995 --> 12:09.562
But I need one thing from you.

12:09.596 --> 12:11.564
Young gun in there--

12:11.598 --> 12:12.800
he could use a little
peer mentorship,

12:12.833 --> 12:15.402
help learn the ropes
of the game.

12:15.435 --> 12:18.405
There's not a white boy in the
world that needs help from me.

12:18.438 --> 12:22.209
My mom and dad
taught me that much.

12:22.242 --> 12:24.744
Blake's from Chicago.
He's the real deal.

12:24.778 --> 12:26.479
Being from the Chi
and looking like him

12:26.513 --> 12:28.916
ain't the same as being from
the Chi and looking like me.

12:28.949 --> 12:31.584
-Lucious and Cookie
taught me that, too.
-(chuckles)

12:31.618 --> 12:34.254
He wasn't raised by a Lucious.
Or even a Cookie.

12:34.287 --> 12:35.755
The streets raised him.

12:35.789 --> 12:37.724
See them tats?

12:37.757 --> 12:39.592
It's to cover up
three bullet holes.

12:39.626 --> 12:42.229
He says music
is gonna save his life.

12:42.262 --> 12:45.332
For the record, I don't
deal with no culture vultures.

