-Okay.
-All right?

27:26.478 --> 27:27.579
-Yeah.
-Let's try another one.

27:33.219 --> 27:34.653
(grunts)

27:37.556 --> 27:39.625
-Right, right.
-LUCIOUS: I'm telling you,

27:39.658 --> 27:41.828
this is a waste of time.

27:41.861 --> 27:45.064
Well, I'll do the talking
this time.

27:47.666 --> 27:51.403
ANDRE:
Hello. Hi. Hi.

27:51.437 --> 27:53.840
Um, I think we might've gotten
off on the wrong foot.

27:53.873 --> 27:55.307
I apologize for that.
I'm Andre Lyon.

27:55.341 --> 27:58.244
I thought I recognized you.

27:58.277 --> 27:59.846
You're the smart Lyon cub.

27:59.879 --> 28:01.513
-Went to Wharton, right?
-That's right, that's right.

28:01.547 --> 28:03.149
I remember you, too.

28:03.182 --> 28:05.852
And might I say, you look
even more beautiful now.

28:05.885 --> 28:08.687
That sounds like one of your
daddy's tired lines.

28:08.721 --> 28:11.223
-You can go.
-We could.

28:11.257 --> 28:12.925
But we're here in the interest
of transparency,

28:12.959 --> 28:15.895
if indeed She Dragon
is your company.

28:15.928 --> 28:19.098
Armando, can you give us
a moment, please?

28:19.131 --> 28:20.499
Sure.

28:20.532 --> 28:22.234
Thank you, Armando.

28:23.469 --> 28:27.006
Transparency about what,
exactly?

28:27.039 --> 28:29.876
We know that Eddie promised
you'd make a lot of money

28:29.909 --> 28:31.844
from Empire's sale
to Kelly Patel.

28:31.878 --> 28:34.113
Unfortunately, that deal
is not happening.

28:34.146 --> 28:37.649
-Why not?
-Because we shut it down.

28:39.085 --> 28:40.953
Eddie said you were on board.

28:40.987 --> 28:42.388
That we'd all be richer
than God.

28:42.421 --> 28:43.689
Oh, don't worry, um,
we're positive

28:43.722 --> 28:45.691
that Eddie will
take good care of you.

28:45.724 --> 28:49.261
He did give you the same deal
points as Giselle, correct?

28:49.295 --> 28:51.363
What the hell does she
have to do with this?

28:51.397 --> 28:52.698
-Um...
-Yeah,

28:52.731 --> 28:54.733
that-that looks about right,
yeah, Pop?

28:57.403 --> 29:00.873
Um... yeah, I mean, Giselle,

29:00.907 --> 29:02.608
she's got the job at Empire.

29:02.641 --> 29:04.076
Oh, right.
So her-her salary's a bonus

29:04.110 --> 29:05.411
on top of her points, right?

29:05.444 --> 29:06.979
That bitch is getting a salary?

29:07.013 --> 29:09.281
-She's getting, like, $300.
-Uh, four, Pop.

29:09.315 --> 29:11.383
-Four?
-Four, $400,000.

29:11.417 --> 29:12.551
Plus her cut
of the clothing line.

29:12.584 --> 29:13.886
CELESTE:
Oh, hell no.

29:13.920 --> 29:17.389
That no-good son of a...

29:17.423 --> 29:20.292
Broke-ass loses all his money...

29:20.326 --> 29:22.294
-Whoa, lost his money?
-Everything.

29:22.328 --> 29:25.264
His, mine, the ex-wives.

29:25.297 --> 29:27.166
Everything we had was invested

29:27.199 --> 29:28.835
in Steve Lawrence's
Ponzi scheme.

29:28.868 --> 29:32.304
Eddie told me
to sell all my property,

29:32.338 --> 29:34.273
and buy up Empire stock.

29:37.043 --> 29:40.779
And this is how he plays me?
Come on.

29:47.219 --> 29:49.688
PORSHA: The way you talk
about this Burleson,

29:49.721 --> 29:50.857
you would think he live
in a castle

29:50.890 --> 29:52.258
in Transylvania or something.

29:52.291 --> 29:54.126
Just because you have
a nice house

29:54.160 --> 29:56.162
don't make you no less
of a monster.

29:56.195 --> 29:57.629
I thought you didn't even like
this Poundcake.

29:57.663 --> 29:59.131
Why you even going
out the way for her?

29:59.165 --> 30:01.868
We went through a lot
on the inside, okay?

30:01.901 --> 30:03.702
I owe her.

30:03.735 --> 30:05.371
You have no idea.

30:05.404 --> 30:06.538
What I do know:
Lucious gonna kill me

30:06.572 --> 30:08.607
for bringing you out here.

30:08.640 --> 30:09.876
-Give me your hand.
-What're you doing?

30:09.909 --> 30:11.677
What're you doing? Cookie!

30:11.710 --> 30:14.713
(stammers) What am I supposed
to do when he call me?

30:14.746 --> 30:16.448
Keep calm, and he won't call.

30:16.482 --> 30:18.317
Remember,

30:18.350 --> 30:20.786
nice, slow,
steady breaths, okay?

30:20.819 --> 30:21.787
Think happy thoughts.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.022
Pretend like you in the Bahamas.

30:23.055 --> 30:24.190
I don't know, child.

30:24.223 --> 30:25.224
The Bahamas?

30:31.163 --> 30:32.664
(knocking on door)

30:34.766 --> 30:38.570
Uh... (laughs)
Oh, my. You're...

30:38.604 --> 30:40.973
Yeah. Does Mr. Burleson
live here?

30:41.007 --> 30:42.975
BURLESON:
Who is it, Joyce?

30:43.009 --> 30:45.211
Yeah?

30:45.244 --> 30:46.979
(women shouting)

30:47.013 --> 30:48.347
Throw her in the hole.

30:48.380 --> 30:51.417
Holloway? Is that you?

30:51.450 --> 30:54.921
-Oh, my God, it is.
-(chuckling) Yeah.

30:54.954 --> 30:56.722
I can't believe it.

30:56.755 --> 30:57.990
After all these years.

30:58.024 --> 30:59.425
See, now, I told you
I wasn't lying.

30:59.458 --> 31:01.560
Well, come on.
Don't just stand there.

31:01.593 --> 31:02.594
-Come on in.
-Come on in.

31:07.566 --> 31:10.702
So, uh... what brings you here?

31:10.736 --> 31:12.704
You writing a book?
Y-You want an interview

31:12.738 --> 31:14.506
with me or something or...?

31:14.540 --> 31:18.077
It's a nice, uh, life
you have, Burleson.

31:18.110 --> 31:21.613
Bo, please.
Friends call me Bo.

31:21.647 --> 31:22.648
Hmm.

31:24.283 --> 31:25.517
What do your kids call you?

31:25.551 --> 31:26.919
Uh, we don't have any kids.

31:26.953 --> 31:29.455
JOYCE:
That's our one regret.

31:29.488 --> 31:31.457
I just never could get pregnant.

31:31.490 --> 31:34.126
Joyce, honey, come on,
that's not talk for company.

31:34.160 --> 31:37.729
Bo would have made
such a great father.

31:37.763 --> 31:39.531
I could tell by, you know,

31:39.565 --> 31:41.533
how much of a difference
he made to all of you.

31:41.567 --> 31:45.037
Yeah. Yeah, he really
changed our lives.

31:45.071 --> 31:46.472
(Joyce laughs)

31:46.505 --> 31:48.975
I always loved hearing
all about his "girls"

31:49.008 --> 31:50.376
looking up to him for guidance.

31:50.409 --> 31:51.743
I mean, look at you now.

31:51.777 --> 31:53.946
Joyce, I hate to say it,

31:53.980 --> 31:56.915
but I wasn't Bo's favorite.

31:56.949 --> 31:58.750
-No?
-No.

31:58.784 --> 32:02.088
-Poundcake was.
-JOYCE: Poundcake?

32:02.121 --> 32:03.622
You didn't tell her
about Poundcake?

32:03.655 --> 32:06.158
(scoffs) She doesn't want to
hear about those old stories.

32:06.192 --> 32:07.893
Oh, I do want to hear
the stories.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.795
Which one's Poundcake, Bo?

32:09.828 --> 32:11.830
Joyce, honey.

32:11.863 --> 32:14.066
Cookie and I got to talk about
that book she's gonna write.

32:14.100 --> 32:16.335
Oh, where are my manners?

32:16.368 --> 32:17.936
Let me go get you two
some snacks.

32:21.707 --> 32:24.010
Get your hands off me.

32:24.043 --> 32:26.745
What the hell you think you're
trying to pull, Holloway?

32:26.778 --> 32:28.680
Must've seemed like
a real smart idea

32:28.714 --> 32:30.616
up there in that cute little
head of yours, huh?

32:30.649 --> 32:32.851
-You know, it's against the law.
-What?

32:32.884 --> 32:34.420
Ex-convict coming
to C.O.'s house.

32:34.453 --> 32:35.988
Now, you get the hell
out of here.

32:36.022 --> 32:38.324
The next time you step your foot
on my property, I'll shoot you.

32:38.357 --> 32:40.126
You know what?
The days of you scaring me

32:40.159 --> 32:41.927
are long gone, Bo.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.830
I got enough dirt
to put your wrinkly ass away

32:44.863 --> 32:46.598
for the rest of your
miserable life.

32:46.632 --> 32:49.868
Hell, I've had the governor
in my house for dinner.

32:49.901 --> 32:51.637
You want to try me?

32:51.670 --> 32:54.806
You want to see how fast
I could drop a dime on your ass?

32:54.840 --> 32:56.642
What do you want, Holloway?

32:56.675 --> 32:59.311
I want to know what you did
with Poundcake's baby.

32:59.345 --> 33:00.779
And if you don't tell me,

33:00.812 --> 33:03.349
I'll just tell your wife
how that baby came to be.

33:03.382 --> 33:05.184
What the hell
do you think happened?

33:05.217 --> 33:07.053
Prison babies go in the system.

33:07.086 --> 33:08.454
You're lying.

33:08.487 --> 33:10.456
That baby never made it
into the system.

33:10.489 --> 33:12.358
So what did you do, Bo?

33:12.391 --> 33:15.494
Hmm? Did you kill that baby?

33:15.527 --> 33:16.895
I didn't kill no baby.

33:16.928 --> 33:19.065
(whispering): Shh. I wouldn't
do that. (clicks tongue)

33:19.098 --> 33:21.667
What kind of monster
you think I am?

33:24.370 --> 33:26.205
Okay, look...

33:26.238 --> 33:28.407
that baby was half-white,
you know.

33:28.440 --> 33:30.209
-Really?
-The dark kids

33:30.242 --> 33:33.412
go in the system.
The lighter kids got adopted.

33:33.445 --> 33:35.481
They took the white kids
and the lighter-skinned kids,

33:35.514 --> 33:38.016
and they put them into
a special adoption agency.

33:38.050 --> 33:40.986
-Hope House, it's called.
-Hope House?

33:41.019 --> 33:42.821
Yeah, you better hope
you're not lying.

33:42.854 --> 33:47.559
Because if you are,
I will blow your life up.

33:47.593 --> 33:50.096
I got lemonade
and fresh cinnamon pound cake.

33:50.129 --> 33:52.931
Oh, that's so sweet of you,
Joyce, but I can't stay.

33:52.964 --> 33:56.902
You know it's good to know that
Bo still like eating pound cake.

33:56.935 --> 34:00.406
-Have a good one.
-What...?

34:04.243 --> 34:06.212
Okay, Cookie,
can we please go?

34:06.245 --> 34:10.082
So Hope House is legit,
huh, Thirsty?

34:10.116 --> 34:12.518
All right, well, then I need you
to find out what you can

34:12.551 --> 34:15.221
about a mixed-race baby
born on the dates I gave you.

34:15.254 --> 34:17.123
Okay.

34:17.156 --> 34:20.392
Finally, can we go now?

34:20.426 --> 34:21.927
-No.
-No...

34:21.960 --> 34:25.264
I'm not done.
Leave the engine running.

34:28.300 --> 34:29.935
Oh. Uh, let me get Bo.

34:29.968 --> 34:31.403
No, no, no, no.

34:31.437 --> 34:33.705
-Joyce, it's you I want
to talk to. -Oh, I don't know.

34:33.739 --> 34:36.708
I, uh... I don't want to get
in the middle of anything here.

34:36.742 --> 34:39.645
Your husband is a rapist.

34:39.678 --> 34:41.313
He beat us. He tortured us.

34:41.347 --> 34:43.081
He raped lots of girls
in prison.

34:43.115 --> 34:47.052
He raped this one girl,
Poundcake. They had a baby.

34:47.085 --> 34:48.487
He took it from her

34:48.520 --> 34:51.089
and sold it to some
baby brokers.

34:51.123 --> 34:54.326
-No.
-You should get out of this.

34:54.360 --> 34:56.228
You need to leave him.
Your husband...

34:56.262 --> 34:57.863
What the hell are you doing?

35:00.699 --> 35:02.768
Believe me.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.910
LUCIOUS:
This is crazy.

35:11.943 --> 35:14.913
I mean, Eddie had ten
shell companies set up.

35:14.946 --> 35:16.515
I mean, he had some plan

35:16.548 --> 35:19.117
in which he was gonna
put himself way back on top.

35:19.151 --> 35:21.953
Yeah, a plan that exposed Empire
to an insider trading scandal,

35:21.987 --> 35:23.822
could've gotten us all
thrown in prison.

35:23.855 --> 35:26.658
You need to give Eddie
his walking papers, Pop.

35:30.962 --> 35:34.300
Hey, Dre, you remember
when you were, like, um...

35:34.333 --> 35:35.934
nine or ten

35:35.967 --> 35:38.604
and the police raided our house
and you hid my gun

35:38.637 --> 35:41.139
inside of your box of Legos?

35:41.173 --> 35:44.276
Yeah, I remember.

35:44.310 --> 35:47.379
It seemed like you always
had my back back then.

35:47.413 --> 35:50.316
What happened to that boy?

35:50.349 --> 35:52.684
What happened to my son?

35:55.921 --> 35:58.190
(sighs)

35:58.224 --> 36:01.493
March 22, 2005,

36:01.527 --> 36:03.262
11:37 a.m.

36:04.763 --> 36:07.899
That's the moment I was
diagnosed with bipolar disorder.

36:07.933 --> 36:11.870
From that day on,
that's all you saw

36:11.903 --> 36:14.706
when you looked at me.

36:14.740 --> 36:16.742
Damaged son.

36:16.775 --> 36:19.511
But you are damaged.

36:19.545 --> 36:21.580
And what about you?

36:21.613 --> 36:25.150
Your sickness is so deep.

36:25.183 --> 36:27.419
You're a sociopath.

36:27.453 --> 36:30.656
You have no remorse
for anything you do,

36:30.689 --> 36:32.524
ever.

36:39.064 --> 36:41.767
You sound pretty damaged
to me, too, Pop.

36:48.274 --> 36:49.841
* Okay, I'm going to the top *

36:49.875 --> 36:51.176
* I'm-a never stop *

36:51.209 --> 36:53.445
* Plus you got the swag
of an undercover cop *

36:53.479 --> 36:55.113
* Or a plumber or an opp *

36:55.146 --> 36:57.182
* The dude from
Dumb and Dumber-- hold up *

36:57.215 --> 36:59.685
* No wonder you got
the floor covered, you a mop. *

36:59.718 --> 37:00.786
We got it.

37:00.819 --> 37:02.721
-(applause)
-Bring it in.

37:02.754 --> 37:04.222
Yup.

37:04.256 --> 37:07.759
Hey, I told you,
hard work pays off, gentlemen.

37:07.793 --> 37:10.762
-Good stuff, boy.
-Yeah. So...

37:10.796 --> 37:12.631
being that this is the end
of a hard day's work,

37:12.664 --> 37:16.234
off to the strip club we go!
(laughs)

37:16.268 --> 37:17.869
Unless you still
locked down, right?

37:17.903 --> 37:19.705
-Stop that, bruh.
-(laughs)

37:19.738 --> 37:21.139
Come on, let's move.

37:23.475 --> 37:24.943
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

37:24.976 --> 37:26.945
Where you think you going,
grasshopper?

37:26.978 --> 37:28.747
You got dues to pay.
Look around.

37:30.349 --> 37:32.050
I got to clean this up?

37:32.083 --> 37:34.320
Hey, don't ask me.
That's your sensei now.

37:34.353 --> 37:36.322
Nah. Start with the ashes
in the carpet.

37:36.355 --> 37:37.989
-(sighs)
-My dad hates that.

37:38.023 --> 37:39.825
Enjoy.

37:39.858 --> 37:41.660
So I'm not going
to the strip club?

37:42.994 --> 37:44.129
(sighs)

37:46.465 --> 37:48.634
SHINE: Hey, man, you gonna love
this club, just opened up.

37:48.667 --> 37:50.936
The girls is out of control.
Wait till you see Cinnamon.

37:50.969 --> 37:53.472
(indistinct chatter)

37:53.505 --> 37:56.174
-I'm gonna catch up with you.
-Yo, where you going?

37:56.207 --> 37:59.244
Hey, hold up. Wait...

37:59.277 --> 38:01.279
Whipped.

38:01.313 --> 38:02.948
MAN:
For real, man.

38:07.319 --> 38:09.321
(Tiana gasps)

38:09.355 --> 38:11.022
You okay?

38:13.124 --> 38:14.760
Yeah, I'm fine.

38:14.793 --> 38:18.296
What, are you back
to take back what you own?

38:18.330 --> 38:19.931
You should probably
get some rest.

38:19.965 --> 38:21.367
No, I shouldn't.

38:21.400 --> 38:22.801
Everything has to be right.

38:22.834 --> 38:25.471
The-the costumes,
the lighting, the moves.

38:25.504 --> 38:27.439
And right now, it's all wrong.

38:27.473 --> 38:29.608
People out here doing
the best they can for you.

38:29.641 --> 38:33.178
You cursing folks out.

38:33.211 --> 38:35.881
Firing folks on the spot.

38:35.914 --> 38:37.449
That's not the girl I know.

38:37.483 --> 38:39.885
I'm not that girl
anymore, Hakeem.

38:39.918 --> 38:42.287
Eddie saw something in me,

38:42.320 --> 38:44.690
and he promised that
if I just stay focused,

38:44.723 --> 38:46.157
that he'd get me here.

38:46.191 --> 38:49.995
Okay, no distractions.

38:50.028 --> 38:52.498
That's why you turned down
my proposal?

38:52.531 --> 38:55.567
Everything is not about you.

38:55.601 --> 38:59.004
Eddie knows what I have to do
to get what I want.

38:59.037 --> 39:02.040
Now, if you'll excuse me, I'm
gonna get back to my rehearsal.

39:04.209 --> 39:05.777
Okay.

39:22.928 --> 39:25.831
* This is how it feel to have
a winning streak, baby *

39:25.864 --> 39:27.899
* Rockin' ...
you can't pull off... *

39:27.933 --> 39:29.568
Hey, how you doing?

39:29.601 --> 39:31.770
-It's good to see you.
-Jamal Lyon, DJ Selection.

39:31.803 --> 39:33.338
What's up, man.
Thank you for having us.

39:33.371 --> 39:36.708
-Welcome to my den of misfits.
-Can you play this track, love?

39:36.742 --> 39:38.544
-Who's the artist?
-It's a new artist.

39:38.577 --> 39:40.879
Who'd like to remain anonymous
for the time being.

39:40.912 --> 39:43.415
* Rings, got a few on *

39:43.449 --> 39:45.717
* Got gold like a leprechaun,
my girl got a leopard on... *

39:45.751 --> 39:47.252
All right, y'all.

39:47.285 --> 39:50.355
We got an exclusive
here tonight.

39:50.388 --> 39:51.957
No introductions needed.

39:51.990 --> 39:54.159
You already know what to do.
So let's go.

39:56.261 --> 39:58.964
* They could see us
falling out *

39:58.997 --> 40:01.066
* But I can see us
fall tonight *

40:01.099 --> 40:04.636
* They could see us
coming down *

40:04.670 --> 40:07.038
* But I could see us
going higher *

40:07.072 --> 40:09.708
* Selfish teardrops *

40:09.741 --> 40:12.478
* Fall from memories *

40:12.511 --> 40:14.980
* I broke your heart *

40:15.013 --> 40:17.115
* But no more crying now *

40:17.148 --> 40:18.484
(crowd cheers)

40:18.517 --> 40:21.286
* They think our picture
is broken *

40:21.319 --> 40:23.288
* But maybe it was
out of focus *

40:23.321 --> 40:25.390
* They don't know we're gold *

40:25.423 --> 40:26.892
* They don't know
we're gold... *

40:26.925 --> 40:27.893
* Yeah *

40:27.926 --> 40:29.127
You think Empire's
ready for this?

40:29.160 --> 40:31.963
It don't really matter,
'cause I am.

40:31.997 --> 40:34.466
What'd y'all think?
How'd y'all like it?

40:34.500 --> 40:36.468
* They don't know we're gold,
they don't know we're gold *

40:36.502 --> 40:39.137
* They don't know we're gold. *

40:39.170 --> 40:40.939
(door closes)

40:44.843 --> 40:47.646
-Baby?
-Yeah?

40:47.679 --> 40:48.847
What, you over here working?

40:48.880 --> 40:50.281
You sure your cardiologist
would approve?

40:50.315 --> 40:51.617
No, I'm just putting some money

40:51.650 --> 40:52.918
on the books for some girls

40:52.951 --> 40:54.185
still behind the wall,
that's all.

40:54.219 --> 40:55.954
Somebody shaking you down?

40:55.987 --> 40:57.956
(laughs):
No. Not at all.

40:57.989 --> 40:59.925
So, um...

40:59.958 --> 41:03.194
How did today go?

41:03.228 --> 41:06.464
It was good. It was good.

41:06.498 --> 41:08.500
Okay.

41:13.238 --> 41:15.440
You gonna let me just
walk away with that?

41:15.473 --> 41:18.343
Are you okay, baby?

41:18.376 --> 41:22.347
I saw two women today.

41:22.380 --> 41:24.349
One was dying,

41:24.382 --> 41:26.184
and one was just living a lie.

41:26.217 --> 41:29.955
And after all of this stuff
that happened with my heart

41:29.988 --> 41:33.859
and seeing those women,
I just...

41:33.892 --> 41:36.494
I don't want to take my life
for granted anymore.

41:36.528 --> 41:37.729
And Lucious,
I hear you saying

41:37.763 --> 41:39.497
you want me back
and you want things

41:39.531 --> 41:42.834
back the way they were, but I'm
not interested in going back.

41:42.868 --> 41:44.402
I-I want to move forward.

41:44.435 --> 41:46.071
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
What are you saying?

41:46.104 --> 41:49.340
-I mean, are you...
-What?

41:49.374 --> 41:50.909
You're saying you don't want
to be with me anymore?

41:50.942 --> 41:52.010
Is that what...

41:52.043 --> 41:53.545
That's not what I said, Lucious.

41:53.579 --> 41:55.246
For a minute, I thought you were

41:55.280 --> 41:57.215
winding up to sing me
some swan song.

41:57.248 --> 41:58.216
I'm... Look.

41:58.249 --> 42:01.987
I'm being serious. Okay?

42:02.020 --> 42:03.722
I love you.

42:03.755 --> 42:05.557
I do, but I don't

42:05.591 --> 42:07.726
want things to go back
to the way they were

42:07.759 --> 42:10.862
because I can't deal with
the lies and the cheating and...

42:10.896 --> 42:12.931
and the competition.

42:12.964 --> 42:15.867
I just...
(sighs)

42:15.901 --> 42:18.503
I just need things to be better.

42:18.536 --> 42:20.405
You are my better.

42:20.438 --> 42:23.208
I don't want half
of what's yours.

42:23.241 --> 42:26.678
I need to share what's ours.

42:26.712 --> 42:29.681
I want to be your partner
in business

42:29.715 --> 42:31.482
and in life.

42:32.884 --> 42:36.254
I need your respect, Lucious.

42:38.757 --> 42:42.160
(sighs)
Cookie.

42:44.462 --> 42:47.633
I respect you

42:47.666 --> 42:51.569
and appreciate you
more than anything in life.

42:51.603 --> 42:53.905
Okay?

43:12.290 --> 43:14.292
*

